transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Hi, thank you for calling Viagra.

Speaker 2: How can I assist you?

Speaker 1: I need to verify and order that I receive the right materials,

Speaker 2: the right prescription.

Speaker 1: Yeah, of course.

Speaker 2: What's your name and date of birth?

Speaker 1: My name is Joseph.

Speaker 2: Last name is Veselka, V as in victory, E-S-E-L-K-A.

Speaker 1: Thank you, Joseph.

Speaker 2: OK, so it looks like you ordered Viagra A-G-V,

Speaker 1: so that's what you should have had received.

Speaker 2: Yes, I should have received, I think,

Speaker 1: I ordered, yes, the new Viagra A-G-V.

Speaker 2: And what I received in the mail today, everything on the label,

Speaker 1: everything on all the literature just

Speaker 2: says it's a standard generic product

Speaker 1: from Apco Pharmaceuticals.

Speaker 2: Nothing A-G-V-ish, nothing is shown on the photos

Speaker 1: that you show online, et cetera.

Speaker 2: So how do I know I got the A-G-V versus the old stuff?

Speaker 1: Yeah, so it should say Greenstone on the label,

Speaker 2: and it should also, every single pill

Speaker 1: should have the number 100 engraved on the tablet.

Speaker 2: No, OK, these do not.

Speaker 1: It should say what on the label?

Speaker 2: I'm sorry?

Speaker 1: Oh, Greenstone LLC, and then the pill

Speaker 2: should have the number 100 engraved on them.

Speaker 1: No, they do not.

Speaker 2: They do not?

Speaker 1: OK, what does your pill say?

Speaker 2: The one side is blank, there's nothing on it,

Speaker 1: and the other one says A-C-340, which when I looked it up

Speaker 2: online, it's just standard generic.

Speaker 1: Yeah, so it looks like they did send you the classic Viagra,

Speaker 2: not the A-G-V-ish.

Speaker 1: Yeah.

Speaker 2: So let me go ahead and correct that, Joseph,

Speaker 1: and I'll ask the pharmacy to reship your order

Speaker 2: at an additional cost, OK?

Speaker 1: Don't worry about having to reship those back to us.

Speaker 2: You can go ahead and keep them or discard them up to you,

Speaker 1: but the pharmacy will be reshipping your order, OK?

Speaker 2: Well, thank you very much for your help.

Speaker 1: I appreciate it so much.

Speaker 2: Of course, you're welcome.

Speaker 1: Joseph, have a nice day.

Speaker 2: Bye.

Speaker 1: You too, bye-bye.
